Revenue collection in Burundi surged
43 percent to 44 billion francs ($34.6 million) in September
from a year earlier, the Burundi Revenue Authority said.  The amount collected was 22 percent above target, the
Bujumbura-based agency said in a statement on its website today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
